reviews.text: Second time booking their Coffee Cart + Bubble Tea service for wedding. Great specialty coffee & drinks, great service all at a great price point. Thanks Julian & Team for making the weddings unique.
Took a latte art class here with Julian and I am very surprised that every student was making some good shapes by the end of 2 hours üôè

Didn't try the coffee. Had the croissants which turned out to be tasty but could be more generous with the fillings. It'll truly fit the phrase hidden gem because the shop is concealed on the second floor of the building. I've only discovered it by chance, despite living just around the corner.

My wife and I attended the Basic Barista & Latte Art at Nineteen95 the Espresso Bar, our first time experience was truly awesome and we surely left this course with a very good impression. Julian was a very very patient trainer and also very determine to find out our pouring mistakes during latte art. He constantly keep finding out what are the root causes in our pouring and gave us various solutions and alternatives to improve our pouring motions. We highly recommend Basic Barista and latte art course and kudos to both the guys at Nineteen95 the Espresso Bar!
